  "body": "After bumping wit-bindgen, every provider crate fails `cargo clippy --target wasm32-wasip2 -- -D warnings` with `unused_imports` on the generated `bindings::exports::*` re-exports. The macro output is correct but clippy sees the exports as dead. Suppressing at the macro site is the obvious fix but it hides real dead code in handler bodies. Looking for a narrower allow.\n",
